## Description {#details}

Interfaces for registering analysis passes, producing common pass manager configurations, and parsing of pass pipelines.

<Link id="l00232" /><CodeLine lineNumber="232"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the code or serious code size growth.</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00234" /><CodeLine lineNumber="234"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Note that \\p Level cannot be &#96;O0&#96; here. The pipelines produced are</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00310" /><CodeLine lineNumber="310"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00311" /><CodeLine lineNumber="311"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Parse a textual pass pipeline description into a \\c</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00312" /><CodeLine lineNumber="312"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// ModulePassManager.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00313" /><CodeLine lineNumber="313"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00314" /><CodeLine lineNumber="314"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The format of the textual pass pipeline description looks something like:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   module(function(instcombine,sroa),dce,cgscc(inliner,function(...)),...)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Pass managers have ()s describing the nest structure of passes. All passes</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// are comma separated. As a special shortcut, if the very first pass is not</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// a module pass (as a module pass manager is), this will automatically form</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the shortest stack of pass managers that allow inserting that first pass.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00322" /><CodeLine lineNumber="322"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// So, assuming function passes &#39;fpassN&#39;, CGSCC passes &#39;cgpassN&#39;, and loop</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00323" /><CodeLine lineNumber="323"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// passes &#39;lpassN&#39;, all of these are valid:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00324" /><CodeLine lineNumber="324"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00325" /><CodeLine lineNumber="325"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   fpass1,fpass2,fpass3</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00326" /><CodeLine lineNumber="326"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   cgpass1,cgpass2,cgpass3</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00327" /><CodeLine lineNumber="327"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   lpass1,lpass2,lpass3</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00328" /><CodeLine lineNumber="328"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00329" /><CodeLine lineNumber="329"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// And they are equivalent to the following (resp.):</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00330" /><CodeLine lineNumber="330"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00331" /><CodeLine lineNumber="331"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   module(function(fpass1,fpass2,fpass3))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00332" /><CodeLine lineNumber="332"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   module(cgscc(cgpass1,cgpass2,cgpass3))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00333" /><CodeLine lineNumber="333"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   module(function(loop(lpass1,lpass2,lpass3)))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00334" /><CodeLine lineNumber="334"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00335" /><CodeLine lineNumber="335"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// This shortcut is especially useful for debugging and testing small pass</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00336" /><CodeLine lineNumber="336"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// combinations.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00337" /><CodeLine lineNumber="337"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00338" /><CodeLine lineNumber="338"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The sequence of passes aren&#39;t necessarily the exact same kind of pass.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="339"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// You can mix different levels implicitly if adaptor passes are defined to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="340"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// make them work. For example,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="341"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="342"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   mpass1,fpass1,fpass2,mpass2,lpass1</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="343"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="344"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// This pipeline uses only one pass manager: the top-level module manager.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="345"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// fpass1,fpass2 and lpass1 are added into the top-level module manager</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="346"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// using only adaptor passes. No nested function/loop pass managers are</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="347"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// added. The purpose is to allow easy pass testing when the user</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="348"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// specifically want the pass to run under a adaptor directly. This is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="349"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// preferred when a pipeline is largely of one type, but one or just a few</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="350"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// passes are of different types(See PassBuilder.cpp for examples).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="351"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/passbuilder/#a9ca0e57e6445ab2fe568e53ba29cc0fd">parsePassPipeline</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a79ab9199d2ba6a1c9cac2b79efc194a3">ModulePassManager</a> &amp;MPM, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> PipelineText);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="352"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="353"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// &#123;&#123;@ Parse a textual pass pipeline description into a specific PassManager</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00354" /><CodeLine lineNumber="354"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00355" /><CodeLine lineNumber="355"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Automatic deduction of an appropriate pass manager stack is not supported.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00356" /><CodeLine lineNumber="356"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// For example, to insert a loop pass &#39;lpass&#39; into a FunctionPassManager,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00357" /><CodeLine lineNumber="357"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// this is the valid pipeline text:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="358"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="359"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///   function(lpass)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="360"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">Error</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/passbuilder/#a9ca0e57e6445ab2fe568e53ba29cc0fd">parsePassPipeline</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a4ded4558d2b58dcdd7a1736aa69a8bc4">CGSCCPassManager</a> &amp;CGPM, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> PipelineText);</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00673" /><CodeLine lineNumber="673"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
